        <li class="active">Types of Elder Abuse</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="row">
        <br>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article-title" style="font-size:xx-large"><i>How to identify</i></div>
            <div class="article" style="text-align:justify">
                Elder abuse is often hidden and difficult to detect because many older people have no knowledge of abuse. Sometimes older people hide their hurt for fear of being found out about the abuse. Watch the behaviour of older people. Abuse can happen without any indication or signs. Here are some signs to help people recognize if an older person is being abused:
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
            <iframe width="400" height="200" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Xw38u2UACJM" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <hr>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article-subtitle">
                Signs of emotional (psychological) abuse:
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article">
                <ul>
                    <li>scare</li>
                    <li>depression or low mood</li>
                    <li>confusion</li>
                    <li>lonely</li>
                    <li>helplessness</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <hr>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article-subtitle">
                Signs of neglect abuse:
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article">
                <ul>
                    <li>thirst, hunger, weight loss</li>
                    <li>not dressed properly</li>
                    <li>living in a dirty or unstable environment</li>
                    <li>health deterioration</li>
                    <li>dehydration or pressure sores</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <hr>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article-subtitle">
                Signs of financial abuse:
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article">
                <ul>
                    <li>belongings lost</li>
                    <li>no money to support basic living</li>
                    <li>large withdrawals</li>
                    <li>property transfer</li>
                    <li>stress or anxiety</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <hr>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article-subtitle">
                Signs of physical abuse:
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article">
                <ul>
                    <li>pain or limited movement</li>
                    <li>scars</li>
                    <li>unexplained accident</li>
                    <li>unexplained injuriesr</li>
                    <li>an overdose of a sedative</li>
                    <li>fear or anxiety</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <hr>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article-subtitle">
                Signs of social abuse:
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article">
                <ul>
                    <li>feeling sad when you lose touch with others</li>
                    <li>withdrawal or listlessness</li>
                    <li>loss of self-esteem</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <hr>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article-subtitle">
                Signs of sexual abuse:
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="article">
                <ul>
                    <li>sexual diseases of unknown origin</li>
                    <li>urinary incontinence</li>
                    <li>internal injuries</li>
                    <li>scars</li>
                    <li>blood appears in underwear</li>
                    <li>fear of approaching the abuser</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <hr />
    <div>
        Resource:<br>
                 <a href="https://toolkit.seniorsrights.org.au/toolkit/signs-of-elder-abuse/">https://toolkit.seniorsrights.org.au/toolkit/signs-of-elder-abuse/</a><br>
    </div>


</div>